commit_message:
Update developer documentation

Tell users to pull docker-compose from Docker Inc.
Recommend rc3 or greater
Tell users the thread where the bump releases are being discussed
Fix typo in libvirtd

Change-Id: Ib47d3a57452a4266db2b47b41a789908365fda9b

commit_message:
Fix the doc wrong refer marker

The refer is not work in the doc source code, setup right
code for tox to produce right refer. It can help user to
get good doc reference.

Refer http://sphinx-doc.org/markup/inline.html for details.

Closes-Bug: #1444285

Change-Id: I86ed35566e942b7ae89592b29f61ee747756079f

puppetlabs-concat, which will have many breaking changes that affect

commit_message:
Pin puppetlabs-concat to 1.2.1 in fixtures

Puppet Labs is in the process of releasing a 2.0.0 version of
puppetlabs-concat, which will have many breaking changes that affect
many dependent modules. Changes have been merged to master, but not yet
released. While we figure out what changes we need to make in our own
modules and wait for updates in dependent modules, we should just pin
to a stable version.

Change-Id: I0f9a65452c71f0d1392dad4e13418065e911a01b

Default log uploaders to LocalStorage

UploaderBase is a common parent and
should not be used directly.

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 12606, 'date': '2014-11-12 07:25:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Christopher, I have a proposal to modify the way Heat sets up the endpoints to generate the 405s and the Allow header automatically.

I'm not familiar with nova code, but can you take a quick look at my proposal and see if something like that is feasible for nova? Link: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/120914/"}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2014-11-12 15:57:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Christopher, I'd agree with you if your argument was predicated on anything other than convenience. This recommendation should absolutely be included. This is the real expected behaviour of RESTful APIs. Just because Nova (and others) have been doing it wrong doesn't mean we shouldn't include this.

There are cases where returning a 404 (when not expected) is fine with me. An example would be when returning a 401 could potentially expose personal/security sensitive data. This isn't one of those cases. The method for the route is undefined and is implicitly not allowed on that resource. We shouldn't be returning a 404."}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2014-11-13 11:21:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

I agree with Ian that we should make recommendation based on correct or even ideal behavior, not on incorrect precedents set by what is arguably bad code.

I suspect many of the bad behaviors are the result of inadequate frameworks being used to support the APIs. I would hope that one of the outcomes of this working group process are guidelines which make it possible to evaluate and potentially reject tooling that just doesn't measure up.

The spec says that if you return a 405, then you must return an Allow header.

If the URI exists, but the method is not allowed, 405 is the only thing that makes sense."}, {'account_id': 5292, 'date': '2014-11-14 11:39:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Miguel - I'm not sure, the Nova code is different enough its not immediately clear if its applicable.

Ian - its not just a matter of convenience but manpower as well. We have something like 70 extensions in Nova, some of which extend other extensions. So its probably not even a simple matter of looking at each controller individually. If someone volunteers to do it and implements it in a way that is automated and requires no per plugin specific code (a bit of inheritance or something is probably ok) then it'll be happily accepted, but I can't see it being a priority for us given we have much bigger things we need to fix.

Anyway happy with it being the long term direction we want to head in which I guess for many of the older project a lot of the guidelines will just be long term goals because of backwards compatibility issues."}, {'account_id': 12606, 'date': '2014-11-14 15:13:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Christopher, in any case, these guidelines do not need to be influenced by current architectural problems in our APIs, so I was hoping you would reconsider and give your approval, with the understanding that it may take Nova a great effort to comply.'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2014-11-14 15:25:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Christopher, the other itme to consider is that the WG is not here to standardize existing practices. It's to create recommendations going forward that will ideally guide existing APIs as they grow and help them recognize and fix parts that are currently poorly designed. The goal of the group is to not penalize any particular project but to describe the ideal API standards for the entirety of OpenStack. I recognize how large Nova is, and I appreciate your concern for how this may affect Nova, but given that these are recommendations for an ideal, not something that every existing API will have to immediately implement, I think you're too worried about something that will not adversely affect Nova."}, {'account_id': 12807, 'date': '2014-11-14 16:11:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2014-11-17 22:51:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 5292, 'date': '2014-11-17 23:33:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

So I'm ok with this being a guideline, would be opposed to it become a requirement for the forseaable future though. Could maybe add some rationale about it being hard to implement for some existing projects and they'll need to be given some time to get there...."}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-11-18 17:53:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Fleshed out the http section a bit more

Recommended the 405 status code that is used when a valid resource URI
is invoked with an invalid request method.

commit_message:
Configure stable branch ACLs for non-Oslo libs

Now that we are releasing stable branches of all of our libraries, we
need to configure the permissions in those branches to use the
stable-maint teams.

For projects with foo-stable-maint, use those teams.

For projects with foo-milestone, use those teams.

For projects with neither, amend the ACLs without making them exclusive
to add stable-maint-core and leave foo-core.

Also remove the blocks related to "proposed" branches, since we don't
use those for libraries.

Change-Id: I6fb79132d954c8cccdbd0c0584aa7acbe4655fef

commit_message:
Accept unit test command as an input in the CLI during 'app create'

Accept the unit test command, as a '--unittest-cmd' flag during
'app create'

Today, the only way we can use the unittest feature is by providing
the test command in the planfile.

User should be able to pass in a test command on the command line.

Change-Id: I5d14adf51f8155f355fafbcfe74054c48188a22a
Closes-bug: 1444613

commit_message:
Temporarily copy proposed/* ACLs to stable/kilo

The proposed/kilo branches of integrated release projects will not
be used this cycle. Instead we're going straight into stable/kilo
but keeping the access controls we had over the old proposed
branches for now. This change can be reverted once Kilo is released,
to return control to teh stable branch maintainers thereafter.

Change-Id: Iaced68397d700d19a3f715de458bd83cbf78cf39

commit_message:
Use 'set' instead of 'list' to speed up image query

It's a tiny improvement. But given it's harmless and the image list query
will be called many times. So it would be nice to have it.

commit_message:
pep8: fixed multiple violations

Fixed violations:
* E128 continuation line under-indented for visual indent
* E251 unexpected spaces around keyword / parameter equals
* E265 block comment should start with '# '
* E713 test for membership should be 'not in'
* F402 import shadowed by loop variable
* H305  imports not grouped correctly
* H307  like imports should be grouped together'
* H402  one line docstring needs punctuation'
* H703  Multiple positional placeholders

Also enabled H803 check that didn't have any violations.

Change-Id: I957ab273ddc61b02763d6b60b21d11ed4e73d472

commit_message:
Expose r/o listener callback + details filter callback

Also makes sure that the kwargs that are returned are
not mutable by returning a copy (which if modified will
have no effect).

commit_message:
Use oslotest instead of common test module

Module openstack.common.test is obsolete, so we should use
oslotest library instead of it.
Modified tests and common database code, new requirement added.

Change-Id: I853e548f11a4c3785eaf75124510a6d789536634

commit_message:
WIP: haproxy reference amphora API client

Fixed the api client to work with haproxy amphora
agent api server:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/160034/

This patch replaces:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/145637/14

This will be the class used to interface with the amphora API

Change-Id: I4f207cd1e9a4ad632190d7e30060b840934d0016
Co-Authored-By: Trevor Vardeman <trevor.vardeman@rackspace.com>
Co-Authored-By: Stephen Balukoff <sbalukoff@bluebox.net>

Here's what going on:

1. There is tempest test, that deletes a Trust and then perform a GET again. It expects a NotFoundException, which is correct.

2. get_trust() returns None if no trust record is found, the logic to raise the NotFound exception is handled manually in the controller code. 

https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/master/keystone/trust/controllers.py#L78

3. After adding the policy check, the policy check for trustee_or_trustor is triggered first before the extra handling in #2.

4. When the policy check is triggered for non-existing trust, it will return none, and since it is empty the policy enforcer raises a Forbidden error.

Henry, I thought maybe the trust information is not getting forced into the the "target" of the policy enforcer. Getting desperate and trying different pattern.

Finally figured out why it is failing on grenade.  

During upgrade the policy file does not get updated.  It is assumed that services should work fine even with the old policy file after the upgrade. And if there are changes on the policy file, we need to have a warning cycle to tell operator what they have to do before we can make the actual code change or a release note and then have operator manually update it.

Here's what I got from sdague:
1. so, you need to put in a warning cycle so that existing clouds work fine, get a warning message that they need to add a thing into policy instead, then do the policy change next cycle.
2. or get the relevant PTL to say this is worth making everyone have to make manual changes and get that added to the release notes

So we might have to go about it this way:
1. update the policy file with the correct policy rule , this won't break keystone since it is not consumed at all
2. have a warning cycle
3. on the next cycle, have keystone consume that policy rule

Have to sort this out with Morgan on how to go about the update of policy file...'}, {'account_id': 1941, 'date': '2015-04-15 19:22:04.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 1941, 'date': '2015-04-15 19:23:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

commit_message:
Make get_trust a protected method

Due to get_trust having an entry in the policy.json file get_trust
should be protected.

Updated the policy file with the correct definition of trust owner
by checking if the user_id is trustor or trustee.

Clean up duplicate checks from controller for get_trust and
list_roles_for_trust, since we already perform the same check in
the policy file.

Use jsonutils from oslo.serialization

Sahara should use jsonutils from oslo_serialization because
it support all functions from json. Also added
hacking check for that.

Closes-bug: 1442120

commit_message:
Add parser/lexer

These files are generated from congress/datalog/Congress.g,
but (i) they change rarely and so no one remembers to run
make and (ii) they require Java to generate.  So it's
better for end-users and most developers to check the files in
and just have the people changing the grammar remember to
check in the generated files.

Closes-bug: 1387209
Change-Id: Ia315fc28570edfaa7d8b223c46f514fb7e34921e

commit_message:
The output template is close to HOT template

heat-translator output is now generated exactly the
same way as we insert (used OrderedDict instead of dict)
eg: output section at the end
    type comes before properties of resources
Added a testcase to compare generated translator output
and expected hot output template

Change-Id: Iba2e4bc73c471f3e3064a9481fc397ad08470c7a
Closes-Bug: #1355542

commit_message:
Don't run gate-tempest-dsvm-full-ceph job on stable icehouse/juno

Commit 3a2e8120d9302bdc1f6f77c2072eb1b056d8ef0a disable the ceph job
from running in stable/icehouse and stable/juno on the check queue.

However, commit f6391d082e4c4cacc03d926274208de1e968c8a9 made the job
voting in the check *and* gate queues, so the ceph gate job is running
and voting in stable (and failing).

Related-Bug: #1439371

Change-Id: If0dcb9fb40e20082c01f254a0c2c5784240cc957

Omit 'locations' as image-create parameter

Based on current implementation, locations is reserved
attribute, so it should not be a parameter for image
create.

Closes-Bug: #1399778

commit_message:
Use new bind endpoints for dashboard

Use the new http and https bind endpoints for dashboard that are
defined in the Common cookbook.  These will allow more control and
consistency with the other bind endpoints for openstack services.

Change-Id: I15c0c2c40a88e18ff9805d48c4da83890b7f4da7
Partial-Bug: #1430422

commit_message:
Fix python3 tests now that eventlet is fixed

Mock is part of the standard library now.

We still retain python3 test-requirements because qpid cannot be
installed.

Change-Id: I34fa04ecd0b2951be8dc891e14610ff2b5730d3c

commit_message:
Add + use helper to raise + chain exceptions

Ensure that on python versions that can retain
the exceptions associated chain/causes that we make
an attempt to retain them, on versions of python
that do not have this at least attempt to retain the
chain (but we will not get the nice stack formatting
that comes along with that).

Change-Id: I7b46854c3969463009c39be28a3131d2d3179c82

  *Add wf_spec.get_tags() to values in _create_or_update_workflows

commit_message:
Pass migrate_data to pre_live_migration

Commit ebfa09fa197a1d88d1b3ab1f308232c3df7dc009 added an RPC proxy but
as part of that was passing migrate_data=None for pre_live_migration
which breaks live block migration when not using shared storage.

Closes-Bug: #984996

Change-Id: I2a83f1fb0e4468f9a6c67a188af725c3406139d1
(cherry picked from commit 4e515ec2269a1c3187ee9ffad3a6be059ec74b0b)

There was a mismatch in the V4 proxy in the call signatures of this
function. This was missed because the "destination" parameter is passed
in the rpcapi as the host to contact, which is consumed by the rpc
layer and not passed. Since it was not called one of the standard

'}]
commit_message:
Fix check_can_live_migrate_destination() in ComputeV4Proxy

There was a mismatch in the V4 proxy in the call signatures of this
function. This was missed because the "destination" parameter is passed
in the rpcapi as the host to contact, which is consumed by the rpc
layer and not passed. Since it was not called one of the standard
names (either host if to be not passed, or host_param if to be passed),
this was missed.

Change-Id: Idf2160934dade650ed02b672f3b64cb26247f8e6
Closes-Bug: #1442602
(cherry picked from commit 0c08f7f2ef070f7c6172d7742f9789e0a8bda91a)

commit_message:
backend_argument should be marked secret

Since the backend_argument can potentially contain a password,
it should be marked secret to avoid leakage into the logs.

Closes-Bug: #1443598

Change-Id: I55663db4cf2df84a66de8f64fba4b4f129ae827d
(cherry picked from commit f9db1a65bd4d83d12c572ba4d5807845996ef410)

[{'created': '2015-04-10 20:38:49.000000000', 'message': 'Release bdm constraint source and dest type

https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1377958 fixed a problem
that source_type: image, destination_type: local is not
supported for boot instance, exception should be raised to
reject the param otherwise it will lead to instance become
ERROR state.

However the fix introduced a problem on nova client
https://bugs.launchpad.net/python-novaclient/+bug/1418484
The fix of the bug leads to following command become invalid

nova boot test-vm --flavor m1.medium --image centos-vm-32
--nic net-id=c3f40e33-d535-4217-916b-1450b8cd3987 --block-device
id=26b7b917-2794-452a-95e5-2efb2ca6e32d,bus=sata,source=volume,bootindex=1

So we need to release the original constraint to allow
the above special case pass the validation check then
we can revert the nova client exception
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/165932/)

This patch checks the boot_index and whether image param is
given after we found the bdm has source_type: image,
destination_type: local, if this is the special case, then
no exception will be raised.

Closes-Bug: #1433609

Change-Id: If43faae95169bc3864449a8364975f5c887aac14
(cherry picked from commit cadbcc440a2fcfb8532f38111999a06557fbafc2)

commit_message:
Release bdm constraint source and dest type

https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1377958 fixed a problem
that source_type: image, destination_type: local is not
supported for boot instance, exception should be raised to
reject the param otherwise it will lead to instance become
ERROR state.

However the fix introduced a problem on nova client
https://bugs.launchpad.net/python-novaclient/+bug/1418484
The fix of the bug leads to following command become invalid

nova boot test-vm --flavor m1.medium --image centos-vm-32
--nic net-id=c3f40e33-d535-4217-916b-1450b8cd3987 --block-device
id=26b7b917-2794-452a-95e5-2efb2ca6e32d,bus=sata,source=volume,bootindex=1

So we need to release the original constraint to allow
the above special case pass the validation check then
we can revert the nova client exception
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/165932/)

This patch checks the boot_index and whether image param is
given after we found the bdm has source_type: image,
destination_type: local, if this is the special case, then
no exception will be raised.

Closes-Bug: #1433609

Change-Id: If43faae95169bc3864449a8364975f5c887aac14
(cherry picked from commit cadbcc440a2fcfb8532f38111999a06557fbafc2)

commit_message:
WebSSO should use remote_id_attribute by protocol

WebSSO always use the remote_id_attribute from the
[federation] group. Fix the issue, by consuming the
protocol specific remote_id_attribute if available.

Change-Id: Icdc693965ec53e5ff8f1901af26c9232a20aef7e
Closes-Bug: #1441827
(cherry picked from commit 9b11d13856034e3a2cf6ab1f6ca80a6965818d17)

[{'created': '2015-04-15 03:25:25.000000000', 'message': 'Add min/max of API microversions to version API

As nova-spec api-microversions, versions API needs to expose minimum
and maximum microversions to version API, because clients need to
know available microversions through the API. That is very important
for the interoperability.
This patch adds these versions as the nova-spec mentioned.

Note:
  As v2(not v2.1) API change manner, we have added new extensions if
  changing API. However, this patch doesn't add a new extension even
  if adding new parameters "version" and "min_version" because version
  API is independent from both v2 and v2.1 APIs.

Change-Id: Id464a07d624d0e228fe0aa66a04c8e51f292ba0c
Closes-Bug: #1443375
(cherry picked from commit 1830870718fe7472b47037f3331cfe59b5bdda07)
(cherry picked from commit 853671e912c6ad9a4605acad2575417911875cdd)
'}]
commit_message:
Add min/max of API microversions to version API

As nova-spec api-microversions, versions API needs to expose minimum
and maximum microversions to version API, because clients need to
know available microversions through the API. That is very important
for the interoperability.
This patch adds these versions as the nova-spec mentioned.

Note:
  As v2(not v2.1) API change manner, we have added new extensions if
  changing API. However, this patch doesn't add a new extension even
  if adding new parameters "version" and "min_version" because version
  API is independent from both v2 and v2.1 APIs.

Change-Id: Id464a07d624d0e228fe0aa66a04c8e51f292ba0c
Closes-Bug: #1443375
(cherry picked from commit 1830870718fe7472b47037f3331cfe59b5bdda07)
(cherry picked from commit 853671e912c6ad9a4605acad2575417911875cdd)

have been created, and an attempt is made to launch instances

commit_message:
Add an index to virtual_interfaces.uuid

Performance issues have been reported such
that the query performed by virtual_interface_get_by_uuid
becomes prohibitively slow after a large (~250K) number of instances
have been created, and an attempt is made to launch instances
in batch.  An index added to uuid shows a dramatic improvement
to this query in EXPLAIN testing.

Cherry-picked from: d65bb6de033deaa5f7cf88bca364fc80cf0b2f75

Change-Id: I0bac6f21c5b52ca6691e23b8a0dc68f001d14c18

commit_message:
VMware: Fix attribute error in resize

The class DatastorePath was recently removed from ds_util as it's
available in oslo.vmware. One of the reference was missed during
the refactor.

Change-Id: Idc5825c304a99e83cbf36e93751148d6f995131a
Closes-Bug: #1440968
(cherry picked from commit ab4a5a5300179a79f7a67688f0e9f3fc280c0efa)

commit_message:
Add locking to PureISCSIDriver around creating Purity Host objects.

This will prevent us from getting conflicting credentials for
connection methods which will result in iSCSI attach operations to fail.

Change-Id: Ia206e7b5ff330c8fccb49ed23a31b120a5c04eb3
Closes-Bug: 1444224
(cherry picked from commit a712afe42833443878898bb42851376cd8615ff9)

In order for users to take advantage of COW volumes created from

and ramdisk_id) are no long stored in the 'properties' dict, but as

commit_message:
Include boot properties from glance v2 images

In order for users to take advantage of COW volumes created from
a glance image, Cinder must be configured to use Glance API version
2 (default is 1). In version 2, the required boot metadata (kernel_id
and ramdisk_id) are no long stored in the 'properties' dict, but as
standalone fields in the GET response from glance. The existing cinder
parser for the glance request is not aware of this and the volume
created form a v2 image will lack this required metadata.

This was causing the recent Ceph CI gate failures for
test_volume_boot_pattern.

Change-Id: I688898b3841691369d73887f7eabdceb05155db1
Closes-Bug: #1439371
(cherry picked from commit ea109b5f24dca93fd6f660bc436a685d6101bcea)

Code changes related to the patch set
I467bb680666ec9bc82e55cfe534d74db29009cce removed the process_router()
method that was being used by the Vyatta Firewall agent code to
update/apply firewall to the Vyatta VRouter when an end user executed
the "Set Gateway" or "Add/Remove interfaces" method on a router.

The current patch set restores the functionality by leveraging
functionality provided by neutron.callbacks.

Change-Id: If3ad35ff08d69b6567350354bc7f4bf7fc71f263
Closes-Bug: #1442043
(cherry picked from commit 650e68b4f7a43b9a54f7bffac4d6055d6951163e)
'}]
commit_message:
Restore Brocade Vyatta firewall functionality

Code changes related to the patch set
I467bb680666ec9bc82e55cfe534d74db29009cce removed the process_router()
method that was being used by the Vyatta Firewall agent code to
update/apply firewall to the Vyatta VRouter when an end user executed
the "Set Gateway" or "Add/Remove interfaces" method on a router.

The current patch set restores the functionality by leveraging
functionality provided by neutron.callbacks.

Change-Id: If3ad35ff08d69b6567350354bc7f4bf7fc71f263
Closes-Bug: #1442043
(cherry picked from commit 650e68b4f7a43b9a54f7bffac4d6055d6951163e)

commit_message:
Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API

Remove the modules and tests that have moved to oslo.log. Replace the
use of oslo.log with the standard library logging module.

Replace calls to LOG.deprecated() with a new function in versionutils
that is copied from the body of the old implementation.

Add fatal_deprecations configuration option to versionutils, where it is
used now instead of the old log module.

Change-Id: I5903f9a9c521789cbf3381d9741a8a5308767e2d
Closes-Bug: #1373120
Blueprint: fix-import-cycle-log-and-versionutils

[{'created': '2015-03-25 19:42:34.000000000', 'message': 'Remove code that moved to oslo.i18n

Remove the modules that went to oslo.i18n and their tests, then update
the other modules and tests to use oslo.i18n.

There are a few cases where other modules that will be deleted from the
incubator for juno had references to gettextutils, especially for their
tests. These are commented out as an expedient way to make the tests
run, in anticipation of the files being removed separately.

Change-Id: Ib80a3f0b0f6e96065e86a9b477aebd8bce1201ba
Closes-Bug: #1371702
'}]
commit_message:
Remove code that moved to oslo.i18n

Remove the modules that went to oslo.i18n and their tests, then update
the other modules and tests to use oslo.i18n.

There are a few cases where other modules that will be deleted from the
incubator for juno had references to gettextutils, especially for their
tests. These are commented out as an expedient way to make the tests
run, in anticipation of the files being removed separately.

Change-Id: Ib80a3f0b0f6e96065e86a9b477aebd8bce1201ba
Closes-Bug: #1371702

[{'created': '2015-03-25 19:42:34.000000000', 'message': 'Enhance versionutils.deprecated to work with classes

If object being decorated is a function, it is processed as before,
otherwise a new class is created which logs deprecated message when
class is instantiated. This change comes with 2 unit tests.

Closes-Bug: #1337889
Change-Id: Ib5cc04bea0ff2ea588618599f4e42df16cb85a0d
'}]
commit_message:
Enhance versionutils.deprecated to work with classes

If object being decorated is a function, it is processed as before,
otherwise a new class is created which logs deprecated message when
class is instantiated. This change comes with 2 unit tests.

Closes-Bug: #1337889
Change-Id: Ib5cc04bea0ff2ea588618599f4e42df16cb85a0d

commit_message:
pep8: fixed multiple violations

Fixed violations:
* E128 continuation line under-indented for visual indent
* E251 unexpected spaces around keyword / parameter equals
* E265 block comment should start with '# '
* E713 test for membership should be 'not in'
* F402 import shadowed by loop variable
* H305  imports not grouped correctly
* H307  like imports should be grouped together'
* H402  one line docstring needs punctuation'
* H703  Multiple positional placeholders

Also enabled H803 check that didn't have any violations.

Change-Id: I957ab273ddc61b02763d6b60b21d11ed4e73d472

[{'created': '2015-04-15 06:37:35.000000000', 'message': 'Verify all quotas before updating the database

Update quota multi-value in one request is not an atomic operation, so
even if a quota is invalid (e.g., volumes has a non-integer value),
some values may change but the response code is 400.

This patch will make sure the quota limits are of integer type for all
the requested quota keys before updating the database.

Closes-Bug: 1432972

(cherry picked from commit 197299985a52535ad995dbd111491b58462f140a)
'}]
commit_message:
Verify all quotas before updating the database

Update quota multi-value in one request is not an atomic operation, so
even if a quota is invalid (e.g., volumes has a non-integer value),
some values may change but the response code is 400.

This patch will make sure the quota limits are of integer type for all
the requested quota keys before updating the database.

Closes-Bug: 1432972
Change-Id: If83af0a80489887098e52b03b9c4012e3ef061b5
(cherry picked from commit 197299985a52535ad995dbd111491b58462f140a)

commit_message:
Fix violations of H302:import only modules

Comment '# noqa' was missed in some files, led to pep8 warning.
And some modules imported non-module. This patch fixes them.
This is output of violation:
http://logs.openstack.org/77/60977/1/check/gate-oslo-incubator-pep8/4a00515/

Change-Id: Id79bca9820853ecd9f0660a855d7bb2fe42ec806

commit_message:
Adds decorator to deprecate functions and methods

The deprecated decorator logs a deprecation message when the callable it
decorates is used. The message will include the release where the callable
was deprecated, the release where is may be removed and possibly an
optional replacement.

Change-Id: Ic6260ce9d8950afa248c0f7842817e7312a4d5a7

commit_message:
Remove vim header

No need to set tabstop 189 times, this can be set in your vimrc file
instead.  Also if set incorrectly gate (pep8 check) will catch your
mistakes.

commit_message:
Add `versionutils` for version compatibility checks

There are a number of different version compatibility checks performed across
OpenStack projects, with Nova alone having at least four within it:

    1) Nova agent version check

    2) XenAPI Dom0 plugin version check

    3) RPC API version check

    4) Nova object version check

Despite similarities between all of these checks, each case chooses to
implement its own.

This patch provides a mechanism for standardizing the version checking process
by providing a single, well-tested function, `is_compatible` that the four
cases listed above (and others) can use instead.

Change-Id: Icc5ff6b7f3914df60f78b9a14806413a063dac0f

Fix violations of H302:import only modules

And some modules imported non-module. This patch fixes them.
This is output of violation:

commit_message:
Adds decorator to deprecate functions and methods

The deprecated decorator logs a deprecation message when the callable it
decorates is used. The message will include the release where the callable
was deprecated, the release where is may be removed and possibly an
optional replacement.

Change-Id: Ic6260ce9d8950afa248c0f7842817e7312a4d5a7

instead.  Also if set incorrectly gate (pep8 check) will catch your
mistakes.

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-25 19:42:34.000000000', 'message': 'Add `versionutils` for version compatibility checks

There are a number of different version compatibility checks performed across
OpenStack projects, with Nova alone having at least four within it:

    1) Nova agent version check

    2) XenAPI Dom0 plugin version check

    3) RPC API version check

    4) Nova object version check

Despite similarities between all of these checks, each case chooses to
implement its own.

This patch provides a mechanism for standardizing the version checking process
by providing a single, well-tested function, `is_compatible` that the four
cases listed above (and others) can use instead.

Change-Id: Icc5ff6b7f3914df60f78b9a14806413a063dac0f
'}]
commit_message:
Add `versionutils` for version compatibility checks

There are a number of different version compatibility checks performed across
OpenStack projects, with Nova alone having at least four within it:

    1) Nova agent version check

    2) XenAPI Dom0 plugin version check

    3) RPC API version check

    4) Nova object version check

Despite similarities between all of these checks, each case chooses to
implement its own.

This patch provides a mechanism for standardizing the version checking process
by providing a single, well-tested function, `is_compatible` that the four
cases listed above (and others) can use instead.

Change-Id: Icc5ff6b7f3914df60f78b9a14806413a063dac0f

commit_message:
Move response code verification to share client

Currently, Tempest tests for Manila do verify response codes for API calls.
Move such verifications to client module to have verifications in one place.
Remove response part from returning data to tests as unnecessary.
Fix all tests that have such verifications.

Change-Id: If9f32c616700afb4f3aa1acd6d5ed96a3ce6783b

commit_message:
Fix sqlalchemy migration script 061 for DB2 backend

DB2 doesn't support alter column type from string to text,
need to add a new column and copy data from old column, and
later remove the old column.

Closes-Bug: #1443252
Change-Id: I7b3edf6bf7ea0efaf96398a83dad9ebe61caaa23

commit_message:
Make SoftwareDeployments work for non-CREATE actions

Currently we only create the deployment if the actions list includes
CREATE, but its valid to create e.g DELETE only deployments, which
curently won't work.  So determine whether to create the deployment
on the resource_id instead of via the action, which resolves this problem.

Closes-Bug: #1444087
(cherry picked from commit 0d4235015065a814f7e76f4a34d422146c58ec72)

Change-Id: Ic572fa7119d2918f28196c90f711084ced6089a3

curently won't work.  So determine whether to create the deployment
on the resource_id instead of via the action, which resolves this problem.

commit_message:
Re-sync Agent Collector's virt dir with Ceilometer

The code in monasca_agent/collector/virt is derived from Ceilometer
code, but has fallen out of date and should be re-merged.

The latest Ceilometer code, and therefore this patch, adds libvirt
support for VM resident memory usage inspection, as well as disk
capacity and utilization.  However, these have yet to be thoroughly
vetted or added to the Agent libvirt plugin as additional VM metrics.

Change-Id: Ia30a6059fe4e54b04cb37851f270a9f57d86ae19

[{'created': '2015-03-24 16:24:35.000000000', 'message': 'VMware NSX: Fix DVR operations

The switch to the community management layer mixin introduced
several bugs in the NSX-mh plugins.
This patch:
1) Stops creating centralized SNAT interfaces for NSX distributed
   routers. The NSX backend does not need those and they therefore
   only waste IPs and create confusion. This is done by providing
   an empty implementation for the relevant methods.
2) Does not query l3-agents when removing router interface. This
   is causing errors during interface removal and preventing router
   removal, as the NSX plugin does not use l3 agents at all.
   This patch provides an empty implementation for the relevant
   method thus preventing the DVR mixin from doing any sort of
   operations pertaining l3 agents.
3) It ensures DVR router interfaces are taken into account in the
   management of metadata network for routers.

Applied for stackforge/vmware-nsx commit id:
e248f87867a74722df243598d6a6d707170ca5ce

Change-Id: If1deca49c1b6951db599362b18e3679f4b06856a
Closes-Bug: #1433550

'}]
commit_message:
VMware NSX: Fix DVR operations

The switch to the community management layer mixin introduced
several bugs in the NSX-mh plugins.
This patch:
1) Stops creating centralized SNAT interfaces for NSX distributed
   routers. The NSX backend does not need those and they therefore
   only waste IPs and create confusion. This is done by providing
   an empty implementation for the relevant methods.
2) Does not query l3-agents when removing router interface. This
   is causing errors during interface removal and preventing router
   removal, as the NSX plugin does not use l3 agents at all.
   This patch provides an empty implementation for the relevant
   method thus preventing the DVR mixin from doing any sort of
   operations pertaining l3 agents.
3) It ensures DVR router interfaces are taken into account in the
   management of metadata network for routers.

Applied for stackforge/vmware-nsx commit id:
e248f87867a74722df243598d6a6d707170ca5ce

Change-Id: If1deca49c1b6951db599362b18e3679f4b06856a
Closes-Bug: #1433550
Closes-Bug: #1433553
Closes-Bug: #1433554

commit_message:
Fix index name the assignment.actor_id table.

If we to generate DB schema from model description, it creates index
named 'ix_assignment_actor_id' for 'actor_id' column 'assignment' table,
but migration script 054 added index 'ix_actor_id' for this column.
The simplest way to fix this difference is to add index name to model
description obviously.

Co-Authored-By: Ilya Pekelny <ipekelny@mirantis.com>

Related-Bug: #1292591
Change-Id: I944b7d2db294af9e30f01ef16925e20265d19270

commit_message:
Use lazy loading of gnocchi project to filterout

Uses lazy loading to avoid failure on dispatcher loading
just because of a transient keystone failure.

Change-Id: I1cea8e4cb514da220339fa95112de06b564f3a30

[{'created': '2015-04-08 22:58:45.000000000', 'message': "Security tests for Order resources

These tests will attempt CRUD operations on Order resources, both
with and without (dummy) project ids, and always without valid tokens.
They should all return HTTP 401s. Added tests to OrdersUnauthedTestCase

commit_message:
Security tests for Order resources

These tests will attempt CRUD operations on Order resources, both
with and without (dummy) project ids, and always without valid tokens.
They should all return HTTP 401s. Added tests to OrdersUnauthedTestCase
class, with 'security' and 'negative' tags for all tests. Refactored test
names to be in line with rest of Barbican functional tests, and now using
behaviors instead of client calls.

Change-Id: Id5aaac89550c60eb80b2148527b7f481ac657335

commit_message:
Use project instead of user for activity filter

We choice to use an user for filtering out the gnocchi activity on swift
because it looks more logical that the application is represented by a
user from the keystone point of view.

But unfortunatly, some samples generated by gnocchi activity and ingested
by the gnocchi dispatcher can have the user_id field empty like
objectstore samples created by the swift pollster.

So this patch uses a project instead of an user to filter the activity of
gnocchi.

Change-Id: If57f905580dfacb099b39524cdb6175f5c2c581f

devstack: Fix the creation of archive policy

When keystone is disable the default archive policy
was not created, this fixes it.

commit_message:
Exception priority moved ahead for L2GW not found

Closes-Bug:1440659
High priority  Exception like L2GatewayNotFound, L2GatewayConnectionExists, NetworkNotFound etc are
moved ahead of segmentation id related exceptions

Change-Id: I583031616c2074c2c18a3917abffae9b55c30b84

commit_message:
add swift resource test script

This is a little lame, but it's basically what javelin 1 & 2 and the
devstack exercises have done in the past. It's enough for now on
sanity checking, and can be enhanced if anyone wants to in the future.

(5 comments)

This looks mostly ok, I like the idea of collapsing all changes to configuration related to this bp in one patch, it makes it easier to review and follow the progress on the bp.

However the changes to the help text give a false information. Because the new options are not actually used yet, we should not say in the help text that the old options are DEPRECATED.
On the opposite, we should state in the help of new options that they are not active yet.

The alternative would be to split into pieces, and add each piece to the first patch where the new configuration is used. But even there it won't fully replace the old option until all callers are updated.

In terms of testing I think we will have to live in the gate with both options set until the migration to the new validation framework is complete."}, {'account_id': 10016, 'date': '2015-02-25 11:42:38.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 22.'}, {'account_id': 10016, 'date': '2015-02-25 11:43:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 22: Code-Review-1

Add new multi ssh configuration options

This patch add new configuration options for the multiple strategies
for ssh access to VMs.

Partially implements: blueprint ssh-auth-strategy

commit_message:
Use 'port' instead of 'ports' to reference port from IPAllocation

'ports' is just confusing as IPAllocation can be associated
with only one port.

Closes-Bug: #1442527
Change-Id: I36bfa65956f54e4b290bb7568499a47eca7c126f

commit_message:
Sync loopingcall from oslo-incubator for os-brick

In order for os-brick to be able to be updated to
use the oslo.log library this updated needs to be made
to update loopingcall to no longer use the old incubator
version of oslo log.

Current HEAD in OSLO:
---------------------
commit:  9117130d7e73a18f0720ecb264a0a85aa26d3816
Date:  Fri Apr 10 11:39:29 2015 +0200
Test loopingcall and threadgroup on Python 3

Changes merged with this patch:
--------------------------------
2fbf5065 -  Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API

Change-Id: I2a26dd6464f9bcb95898b29a1a2e45aee250899f

commit_message:
Update swift-recon doc with more options

The swit-recon tool has had several functional additions
added recently but not all of these have been added to the docs.

This change adds the following options to the manpages:

  --human-readable
  --validate-servers
  --sockstat
  --driveaudit
  --region
  --timeout

Also fixes a typo on line 78 (cop -> copy)

Change-Id: Id083b32a60473ad5a2b9ac1d092528d230521c86

commit_message:
Deprecates 'format' in Javelin image description

Javelin uses the same field to describe disk format and container
format. This only works for ami images. This patch replaces the field
'format' in the resource file with 2 new fields: 'disk_format' and
'container_format'.

For backwards compatibility 'format' is still supported, but marked as
deprecated in the comments of Javelin.

Closes-bug: #1429909

Change-Id: Ic199956d11f8be974374b0f3c2cd7bdfedc90c8d

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-14 08:56:02.000000000', 'message': 'Set standard "swappiness"

One thing that remained somewhat of mystery after recent issues with
the OOM killer & centos7 was why we saw the problem only on RAX and
not hpcloud.

In going through the final telemetry sent from a dying host [1] it is
clear there is swap available, but it is not being used at all.

Closer inspection shows that there is one crucial difference between
HP & RAX centos7 images, and that is the swappiness levels -- which is
set to 0 on RAX and 30 on HP [2].

There is discussion about this around the place; [3] is a good post --
but the upshot is that a swappiness of 0 (swap only when needed) can
lead to certain processes triggering the OOM killer despite some swap
being available.  This matches what we saw on the console, which was
usually mysql getting itself killed (unfortunately I don't believe we
have any console logs gathered during the issue still available).

Swap should really be a last-resort for our CI testing.  Using
cloud-based IO as memory is not going to be performant.  This change
proposes turning swappiness down low for all platforms after we setup
the swap-space; this should ensure its availability for extreme
circumstances but not overuse.

I have related changes to enable better oversight of memory usage of
jobs in the works [4].

[1] http://paste.openstack.org/show/196769/
[2] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/oom-in-rax-centos7-CI-job
[3] http://www.percona.com/blog/2014/04/28/oom-relation-vm-swappiness0-new-kernel/
[4] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/171919/

Change-Id: I09974be88cc590cf9ffbd16db58c19131c9532aa

commit_message:
Set standard "swappiness"

One thing that remained somewhat of mystery after recent issues with
the OOM killer & centos7 was why we saw the problem only on RAX and
not hpcloud.

In going through the final telemetry sent from a dying host [1] it is
clear there is swap available, but it is not being used at all.

Closer inspection shows that there is one crucial difference between
HP & RAX centos7 images, and that is the swappiness levels -- which is
set to 0 on RAX and 30 on HP [2].

There is discussion about this around the place; [3] is a good post --
but the upshot is that a swappiness of 0 (swap only when needed) can
lead to certain processes triggering the OOM killer despite some swap
being available.  This matches what we saw on the console, which was
usually mysql getting itself killed (unfortunately I don't believe we
have any console logs gathered during the issue still available).

Swap should really be a last-resort for our CI testing.  Using
cloud-based IO as memory is not going to be performant.  This change
proposes turning swappiness down low for all platforms after we setup
the swap-space; this should ensure its availability for extreme
circumstances but not overuse.

I have related changes to enable better oversight of memory usage of
jobs in the works [4].

[1] http://paste.openstack.org/show/196769/
[2] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/oom-in-rax-centos7-CI-job
[3] http://www.percona.com/blog/2014/04/28/oom-relation-vm-swappiness0-new-kernel/
[4] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/171919/

Change-Id: I09974be88cc590cf9ffbd16db58c19131c9532aa

commit_message:
Fix a logging issue in ssh_utils

In execute_command method of ssh_utils, the string of LOG.debug()
miss the input command info.

Change-Id: Ia99cfabbe49f8fddb4fcbf75638aa0b5c42b937a

commit_message:
Update pod support a manifest change

Currently, we don't support a manifest change when we update a pod.

This patch fix this problem so that we can update the label or other
useful attributes of a pod.

Partial-Bug: #1444383

Change-Id: I87e220e88bc32d7eee9d37c552aea9920a027056

commit_message:
New docker-py needs a later version of requests library

So running "magnum-template-manage list-templates" in
post_test_hook shows a traceback as mentioned in the
bug linked below. Since the requirements repo is frozen
and not yet open for liberty. We need to work around this
problem for now.

Closes-Bug: #1443729
Change-Id: I3284af4a3e01c6738c2e1bdbf57f1d6e019b6d88

[{'created': '2015-04-15 00:47:29.000000000', 'message': "devstack: Workaround devstack job config issue.

The devstack job needs keystone, mysql, and rabbitmq enabled, but the
current devstack job configuration doesn't have that set.  Enable them
in the devstack plugin settings for now until that patch to
project-config merges.

This should make our devstack job complete successfully.

Change-Id: Ibf857dfabf3bf3fd10b69ea075bfe1ed9a7ace25
"}]
commit_message:
devstack: Workaround devstack job config issue.

The devstack job needs keystone, mysql, and rabbitmq enabled, but the
current devstack job configuration doesn't have that set.  Enable them
in the devstack plugin settings for now until that patch to
project-config merges.

This should make our devstack job complete successfully.

Change-Id: Ibf857dfabf3bf3fd10b69ea075bfe1ed9a7ace25

commit_message:
Make local cache more permanent.

With no cache, this code has to download the entire review history for
a project, which takes a really long time, not to mention it's
generally wasteful.

There was code to keep a local cache, but it expired after an hour.
It would make quick repeated runs go faster, but for the stats I keep
posted for OpenStack projects this didn't help.  I regenerate
everything less often.  My stats site is basically broken because of
how terribly inefficient this is.

This updated code keeps the cache around without expiring it.
Instead, it just updates the cache until it hits the first change that
hasn't changed since our cached version and stops.  This should make
things work much better and allow my stats site to keep working.

Change-Id: I784b99dfabeeca81c779dcfda15f1f20bb736957

commit_message:
Use AF_INET6 if eventlet's green dns/socket module fails

It is safe to assume that if green dns module failed the specified
bind address was an IPv6 address as the module lacks support for IPv6.

Change-Id: I7a048a29f544a596abfb37b9d201aaf91ede0fdf

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-15 12:46:40.000000000', 'message': 'Fix MongoDB setup on nonha setup

Currently a replset parameter is set in mongodb.conf no matter if we are
in a ha or nonha setup. This install fine, but on a nonha setup it prevents
any program from using MongoDB, since no replset has been initialized. It
generates the following error when a program tries to use it :

not master and slaveOk=false

To prevent this issue a replicatset is initialized in both ha and nonha
setup, this way if another MongoDB node is added to the pool, it will be
able to attach automatically

Change-Id: I65e3f1ad35cb0cd31f6771444a0cffdf7569222f
'}]
commit_message:
Fix MongoDB setup on nonha setup

Currently a replset parameter is set in mongodb.conf no matter if we are
in a ha or nonha setup. This install fine, but on a nonha setup it prevents
any program from using MongoDB, since no replset has been initialized. It
generates the following error when a program tries to use it :

not master and slaveOk=false

To prevent this issue a replicatset is initialized in both ha and nonha
setup, this way if another MongoDB node is added to the pool, it will be
able to attach automatically

Change-Id: I65e3f1ad35cb0cd31f6771444a0cffdf7569222f

[{'created': '2014-10-22 09:22:05.000000000', 'message': 'Fix db-sync dependencies

W/o this change, some config changes could
be not synced to db and neutron-server service
start not aligned with db sync process

The solution is to fix the dependencies for
Neutron_config stanzas before db sync exec
and for n-server service - after db sync

Closes-bug: #1384133

Change-Id: I769b6e7ddb567a21a91eeb77375213c131a3d396
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>
'}, {'created': '2014-11-21 11:48:16.000000000', 'message': 'Fix db-sync dependencies

commit_message:
Fix db-sync dependencies

W/o this change, some config changes could
be not synced to db and neutron-server service
start not aligned with db sync process

The solution is to fix the dependencies for
Neutron_config stanzas before db sync exec
and for n-server service - after db sync

Closes-bug: #1384133

Change-Id: I769b6e7ddb567a21a91eeb77375213c131a3d396
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Some cleanup in L3 HA code

This patch addresses the following.
1. removes the un-used variables.
2. process_monitor (argument to KeepalivedManager) is changed to
   a non-default parameter as its used in spawn, disable methods.

Change-Id: I8b130b21965ed3387e994818be947eb95d73a423

commit_message:
Fix db-sync dependencies

W/o this change, some config changes could
be not synced to db and neutron-server service
start not aligned with db sync process

The solution is to fix the dependencies for
Neutron_config stanzas before db sync exec
and for n-server service - after db sync

Closes-bug: #1384133

Change-Id: I769b6e7ddb567a21a91eeb77375213c131a3d396
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>
(cherry picked from commit d7c8d2327a0d46a79ca6519762f088efa8e7373a)

Make neutron_plugin_ml2 before db-sync

W/o this change some of config changes for
ml2 plugin could be not synced to db.

Solution is to add a notify on db-sync
for all Neutron_plugin_ml2 stanzas

Closes-bug: #1384119

Change-Id: I23f6bca99e1c077804011897814649419da326d4
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>
(cherry picked from commit 53688bf2b26682474427f31202756d3217ff20f5)

Conflicts:
	manifests/plugins/ml2.pp

Change-Id: Iea762976c38c82f55b5ed9f28d5b5e2df78c7b4b

commit_message:
Support for custom overcloud heat environments

This patch adds a new OVERCLOUD_CUSTOM_HEAT_ENV option
that can be used to supply a custom heat environment
to devtest_overcloud.sh.

Change-Id: Ia359d154a7e6c28e5f9a10ed4e301433cbfb5c3d

commit_message:
Verify all quotas before updating the database

Update quota multi-value in one request is not an atomic operation, so
even if a quota is invalid (e.g., volumes has a non-integer value),
some values may change but the response code is 400.

This patch will make sure the quota limits are of integer type for all
the requested quota keys before updating the database.

Closes-Bug: 1432972

Increase expected swift balance to 10

- Under some circumstances we can have ring balance greater than 0.00
and it's ok so expected number was changed to 10

commit_message:
Make cache key generator ignore cache argument

This argument pollutes the cache keys with cache:True, which is not
actually relevant to the data requested, and makes invalidation
complicated.

Change-Id: Idd5e20de0fff6d540fadc79a5f30c52ff0e29136

commit_message:
load puppet overcloud heat templates and resource registry

This changes the element to use the new tuskar-load-role [1]
and tuskar-load-seed [2]. Includes the Compute and Controller
puppet roles as the extra-data files required by them. If the
puppet directory exists the puppet resource registry is used
with the puppet specific templates (tuskar roles).

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/165150/
    (I9c143afb52c43e4258c3a6797a9707c08d8dcdaf)

[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/165285/
    (I07450edebd0dacd86bd0b28665eb1aaa3ea30ecb)

Change-Id: Id48d6531d71c09bc43df02f9df6cbbe2d21c3546

commit_message:
[install-guide] [yum] install python-openstackclient

Install python-openstackclient instead of python-keystoneclient.

Partially implements bp installguide-kilo.

Change-Id: I2d65f3434e35d5d37662b2d1091810e4546c5e26

commit_message:
Change Ironic node lookups to support names

Ironic's API has been changed to support a node being
looked up by name or UUID in the form of a general ID.

Added a get_machine method and re-mapped the
pre-existing get_machine_by_uuid method to it.

Incremented the python-ironicclient requirements version as
required to support name based ID lookups.

Change-Id: I765de8c1b0059a6667f66cd4e0695ddf08d96842

commit_message:
[install-guide] [fedora;centos;rhel] use /etc/mysql/conf.d directory

Where available, use the /etc/mysql/conf.d directory for additional
database configuration.

Partially implements bp installguide-kilo.

Change-Id: Ie85cbd1e8f13db82bfc38ea9188e7c0a932f04c4

commit_message:
Add get_subnet() method

Although not currently used directly within shade, users of the
shade library may need to get a subnet by name or ID.

commit_message:
Add sahara buildimages jobs for two more plugins

We're now testing the stability and performance of images building
and we're going to enable this jobs for check and gate as voting
job to ensure that we always have working image building scripts
even from master.

Change-Id: I8028c92e8c436a0843b0320f78abb188c87e2478

commit_message:
Explicitly set Sahara service type to change it

We need to explicitly set the new service type in tempest.conf to
change Sahara service type to more consistent data-processing
(instead of data_processing).

Change-Id: I49c69233107d0b5369fbb981856944d1faaf4bab

Add a method to create a subnet and associated unit tests.

commit_message:
Add meta method obj_list_to_dict

Turns out some data structures returned are actually lists of objects
and we need a method to facilitate the conversion of these data structures.

Change-Id: Icaea889051b75034bb48a138a2cb34c86e4a0453

(1 comment)

Quick question, would importlib.util.LazyLoader work instead of a homegrown one?'}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2015-04-11 03:28:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

Real question: why do we care if v1 setups pull in barbican?'}, {'account_id': 6951, 'date': '2015-04-12 19:18:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

i have same question as doug.'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2015-04-13 14:41:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Quoting my email:

"
I package neutron for RDO, so I use requirements.txt as a suggestion.
My main problem was that python-barbicanclient was not packaged for
RDO when I started looking into the issue, but now that it's packaged
in Fedora [1], the issue is not that significant to me. Of course it's
a wasted dependency installed for nothing (plus its own dependencies),
but that's not a disaster, and if upstream team thinks it's the right
thing to do, let it be so, and I'm happy to abandon the change.

[1]: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1208454"'}, {'account_id': 11302, 'date': '2015-04-13 21:25:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

I believe the operator should not be required to install requirements that do not pertain to its deployment. If lbaas v2 is not enabled barbican should not be installed IMO. I am OK with this change assuming other comments are addressed(LazyLoader, etc..), -1 till then.'}, {'account_id': 6951, 'date': '2015-04-14 00:46:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

so finally get what you're saying.  I was thinking you meant to pull barbican client out of requirements.txt.  You just dont want v1 importing it since it doesn't require it.

If you feel strongly about this we can let this patch in.  I'm indifferent either way, other than v1 being deprecated soon and this hanging around for some reason.  I would suggest adding a nice comment for the class explaining the v1 issue and it can be removed once v1 is gone.

I also worry about setting a precedent, but I do not foresee the plugin importing anything else major like this."}, {'account_id': 10273, 'date': '2015-04-14 04:03:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

This mess is probably partially my fault for rushing this in and not using an actual plugin loader like Stevedore. I had meant to go back and look at this once we had things more stable, but it never happened. Would this problem go away if we did switch to using Stevedore? If so, that is probably the correct long-term solution. Otherwise, I don't see a huge problem letting this in assuming any other comments are addressed."}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2015-04-15 13:29:10.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

My immediate problem (no barbicanclient packaged in fedora) is now solved, so I'm not going to push for the change. We can leave with redundant dependency for now."}]

Lazy load certificate manager plugin

It will allow distributors to avoid e.g. barbicanclient dependency for
non lbaasv2 setups.

Change-Id: I3089d23388b31bc53bfadc97bfba87722e4f1b8b

commit_message:
Use proposed/kilo branch instead of master

Use proposed/kilo branch instead of master so we don't
accidentally grab liberty development bits.  Note that
proposed/kilo on swift does not install, we will need
to investigate this and bump in a separate commit.
Also update global requirements SHA.

Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication

Change-Id: Ia114d72e1036142b39d376362696abd52069c156

commit_message:
Add own block in imports for six overwrites

six library has quite a list of overwrites that provides common
functionality between py2 and py3. Overwriting stdlib functions
should be clearly identified which it is not in current hacking
structure and using explicit six.<something>.<something_else>
does not really help the housekeeping nor readability.

This change introduces own block between stdlib and 3rd party
where such overwrites should happen for clear identification.

Change-Id: I3ae9042e040ada7ff49afad224cd317fd98a51a9

commit_message:
Add storage XAG to npiv

The NPIV flow needs both the FC mapping data as well as the backing
storage devices.  Since pypowervm switched to a default of group=None,
that exposed an issue in the query in the npiv.py file where it was not
retrieving the Fibre Ports.

This update extends the XAG request to include Storage, as well as the
original FC_Mappings.

Change-Id: Iaf08b15183383fc1df8d9b294d2a18140e7b3e31

Remove POWERVM_ATTRS from vm.py

For maintainability, use ATTRS_MAP.keys() instead of the redundant

commit_message:
Fix HAProxy live checker in ha_haproxy_termination

Replaced methodology of checking of haproxy process is exist
    was: ps + grep + line count
    now: check pid file and check via pidof

Change-Id: I3d8533531f35c279da67bd9908a706ff29e01b87
Closes-bug: #1414716

commit_message:
change name from aiopcpu to multinode

aiopcpu is an exceptionally cryptic name that doesn't mean anything to
most people reading test results. multinode is what the job is, and is
much more understandable at first glance.

This changes the naming from aiopcpu => multinode. Should we create a
different kind of multinode test in the future, we can come up with an
appropriate name for it then.

This is safe to change because the devstack-gate logic actually is
fully != 'aio', not == 'aiopcpu'.

Change-Id: Ic7fe31a397af8a14ecf33a4902908ff9c03d11d3

commit_message:
Fix untranslatable string

The word "number" is not marked for translation, we cannot just add
it this way to a string.
Instead create two separate strings.

Change-Id: I0396f1d7405987ed1c57f0344e1c5ebeca30a2e3
Closes-Bug: #1444327

commit_message:
fix combination alarm with operator == 'or'

if combination alarm's operator is 'or', then when evaluating it,
its state should be 'alarm' as long as there is one depended alarm
is triggered.

Change-Id: I87cc29c7556598a937aaea8abc745f4ceaca0531
Closes-Bug: #1442613

Improved fuel_package_updates package

* added package tests to run_tests
* used py.test for test running
* added place for tests
* fixed flake8/hacking issues

Change-Id: I249b7c7d0fdc3cf210274e101ee4af3b40b897ca
Implements: blueprint package-fuel-components

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-09 11:35:46.000000000', 'message': 'Fix for cross-tenant package and class isolation

The database constraints which were present were enforcing the global
uniquness of package FQNs and the names of classes defined in them. This
behavior was not correct, as the uniqueness should be enforced per
tenant, so the same package may be uploaded into two isolated tenants
without affecting each other.

This behavior lead to a very serious security issue: any tenant could
upload a package, leave it private and thus block all other tenants of
the cloud from uploading the package with the same name or even other
packages which contain at least one class in common with it. This could
be used to intentionally block all the operations of Murano on any
public environments.

This fix modifies the package name constraint to be unique only in
combination with owner_id, i.e. makes packages unique per tenant. Also
it removes the class name uniquness check from database (as there is no
cross-DB way to check it in a proper way) and adds a check method in
db.api module instead.

As the packages may be made public, this introduces a potential
collision: if the user owns some package, and there is a public package
with the same fully-qualified-name (or defining same class(es)) then the
class loader of the engine will have to choise between these packages
and/or classes defined in them.
To resolve this collision this commit adds a logic to fetch all the
patching packages and then pick the best match. Packages owned by the
current tenant are the most preferred, then the engine will pick public
packages, and non-owned non-public packages are the least preferred
(there may be no such packages now, they may appear when we add other
ways of package sharing).

Closes-bug: #1440094
Change-Id: I5c9b49642dfb6e955cf0c98b42f418da3b82060a

commit_message:
Fix for cross-tenant package and class isolation

The database constraints which were present were enforcing the global
uniqueness of package FQNs and the names of classes defined in them.
This behavior was not correct, as the uniqueness should be enforced per
tenant, so the same package may be uploaded into two isolated tenants
without affecting each other.

This behavior lead to a very serious security issue: any tenant could
upload a package, leave it private and thus block all other tenants of
the cloud from uploading the package with the same name or even other
packages which contain at least one class in common with it. This could
be used to intentionally block all the operations of Murano on any
public environments.

This fix modifies the package name constraint to be unique only in
combination with owner_id, i.e. makes packages unique per tenant. Also
it removes the class name uniquness check from database (as there is no
cross-DB way to check it in a proper way) and adds a check method in
db.api module instead.

As the packages may be made public, this introduces a potential
collision: if the user owns some package, and there is a public package
with the same fully-qualified-name (or defining same class(es)) then the
class loader of the engine will have to choise between these packages
and/or classes defined in them.
To resolve this collision this commit adds a logic to fetch all the
patching packages and then pick the best match. Packages owned by the
current tenant are the most preferred, then the engine will pick public
packages, and non-owned non-public packages are the least preferred
(there may be no such packages now, they may appear when we add other
ways of package sharing).

Closes-bug: #1440094
Change-Id: I5c9b49642dfb6e955cf0c98b42f418da3b82060a

commit_message:
Fix ownership of /var/log/mysql

The galera role sets root as the owner of /var/log/mysql. This prevents
mysql from writing the slow query log file in that location.

This commit adjusts the ownership of /var/log/mysql so that mysql is
the owner and root is the group.

Closes-bug: #1444313
Change-Id: I33d9e672085f61d7b804e3d5fc2b6d4b7ddca4da

[{'created': '2015-03-20 10:40:18.000000000', 'message': 'Make vip_type in ip_addrs extendable for new types

Change vip assigment logic in openstack.yaml.
Instead of i.e.:
assign_vip = True (haproxy by default)
assign_vrouter_vip = True
we have:
vips = ["haproxy", "vrouter"] (when we want to assign VIP
for haproxy and vrouter) or just do not provide 'vips' parameter
(when we don't want VIP at all).

Closes-Bug: #1430250
Change-Id: I6f7c615684fb42291070521aacf84417f6b88b51

commit_message:
Make vip_type in ip_addrs extendable for new types

Change vip assigment logic in openstack.yaml.
Instead of:
assign_vip = True (haproxy by default)
assign_vrouter_vip = True
we have:
vips = ["haproxy", "vrouter"] (when we want to assign VIP
for haproxy and vrouter) or just do not provide 'vips' parameter
(when we don't want VIP at all).

Closes-Bug: #1430250
Change-Id: I6f7c615684fb42291070521aacf84417f6b88b51

How is this better than the current fatal error?"}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-04-14 18:23:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

@aotto, someone asked me to file a bug on this in a different review.  I prefer the exit semantics but the other review had some arguments against.'}, {'account_id': 7494, 'date': '2015-04-15 00:43:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

@Adrian and @sdake, the most concern is that though we cannot create bay without template, but we can update bay.

The concern is that after the bay was created and all the templates are deleted by mistake, then the end user can still operate those bays.

You may want to get more comments here https://review.openstack.org/#/c/172306/4/magnum/cmd/conductor.py'}, {'account_id': 7049, 'date': '2015-04-15 00:50:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

I think as magnum can support dokcer native operation without any templates support. So I think it is OK to start magnum even template not exist.'}, {'account_id': 7494, 'date': '2015-04-15 00:53:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

There are some discussion in IRC that we can use swarm bay to manage native docker server cluster...'}, {'account_id': 10206, 'date': '2015-04-15 01:03:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I think it is not good to exit conductor when many operations are template independent.

Rather than exiting, we can have a way to add template later. I have tried adding new template but I think we can't enable the template without restarting magnum-conductor.

Adding Andrew for his opinion on this."}, {'account_id': 15697, 'date': '2015-04-15 01:23:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

I agree with Madhuri Kumari. And in the case end-user make a mistake to remove the file,DidMagnum-conductor need to exit?
But we must claim a error,when used the template file.Let end-user can install template file and retry the request.'}, {'account_id': 7049, 'date': '2015-04-15 01:42:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: -Code-Review

What I say is container-create , right now, the magnum container operation not rely any templates. As magnum now call docker-py directly.


If we not allow operate without templates(maybe later). I would agree to not remove exit.'}, {'account_id': 668, 'date': '2015-04-15 10:39:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2

Thanks for the additional remarks. Now that I have more of the backstory, I agree that an error condition is more appropriate than a fatal error i this case. commit_message:
Replace 'Database Service' and 'Database module'  with 'Database service'

According to our conventions
(https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions) the
correct  capitalization is 'Database service'.

Change-Id: I49b7a2c3828255dc13f5661a2fd61fc278280100

commit_message:
Fix https stack trace on python 3.4 client

When using the client with python 3.4 and no ssl compression the following
stack trace ocurrs:

 TypeError: startswith first arg must be bytes or a tuple of bytes, not str

Closes-bug: 1442883
Related-bug: 1357430
Change-Id: I8e28f0bb1f3e866f11851247ce31470ca8c2af4f

commit_message:
Fix client when using no ssl compression

Since the release of the 0.16.1 client, using the 'no ssl compression'
option, whether on the command line, or via the library -- Nova does this by
default -- a stack trace was generated.

Closes-bug: 1442664
Related-bug: 1357430

Change-Id: I2b8ddcb0a7ae3cfccdfc20d3ba476f3b4f4ec32d

commit_message:
Show deprecated warnings when import parser

Classes in parser.py are already split to stack.py and
template.py, it's not recommended to import it.

Closes-Bug: #1442011

'}, {'created': '2015-03-27 14:38:52.000000000', 'message': 'Create system test for Fuel EMC plugin

Add test for plugin which checks cinder configuration
file, needed packages and cinder-volume service layout
across the cluster.
Tests require builded emc plugun.
Additional variables required by plugin test:
 * EMC_PLUGIN_PATH - full path to the builded EMC VNX
 plugin;
 * EMC_SP_A_IP - VNX SP IP Address;
 * EMC_SP_B_IP - VNX secondary SP IP Address;
 * EMC_USERNAME - VNX auth username;
 * EMC_PASSWORD - VNX auth password;
 * EMC_POOL_NAME(optional) - ISCSI pool name.

Note: in case of testing on virtual labs all variables,
except EMC_PLUGIN_PATH, can have fictional values.

Implements: blueprint mos-emc-pugin-test

Change-Id: Ie4270f350d188db3e75afc730e6b72a003bc9e53

commit_message:
Create system test for Fuel EMC plugin

Add test for plugin which checks cinder configuration
file, needed packages and cinder-volume service layout
across the cluster.
Tests require builded emc plugun.
Additional variables required by plugin test:
 * EMC_PLUGIN_PATH - full path to the builded EMC VNX
 plugin;
 * EMC_SP_A_IP - VNX SP IP Address;
 * EMC_SP_B_IP - VNX secondary SP IP Address;
 * EMC_USERNAME - VNX auth username;
 * EMC_PASSWORD - VNX auth password;
 * EMC_POOL_NAME(optional) - ISCSI pool name.

Note: in case of testing on virtual labs all variables,
except EMC_PLUGIN_PATH, can have fictional values.

Implements: blueprint mos-emc-pugin-test

Change-Id: Ie4270f350d188db3e75afc730e6b72a003bc9e53

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-02-18 10:48:00.000000000', 'message': 'libvirt: Make sure volumes are well detected during block migration

Current implementation of live migration in libvirt incorrectly includes
block devices on shared storage (e.g., NFS) when computing destination
storage requirements. Since these volumes are already on shared storage
they do not need to be migrated. As a result, migration fails if the
amount of free space on the shared drive is less than the size of the
volume to be migrated. The problem is addressed by adding a
block_device_info parameter to check_can_live_migrate_source() to allow
volumes to be filtered correctly when computing migration space
requirements.

This only fixes the issue on libvirt: it is unclear whether other
implementations suffer from the same issue.

Thanks to Florent Flament for spotting and fixing an issue while trying out
this patch.

Co-Authored-By: Florent Flament <florent.flament@cloudwatt.com>
Change-Id: Iac7d2cd2a70800fd89864463ca45c030c47411b0
Closes-Bug: #1356552
(cherry picked from commit 671aa9f8b7ca5274696f83bde0d4822ee431b837)

commit_message:
libvirt: Make sure volumes are well detected during block migration

Current implementation of live migration in libvirt incorrectly includes
block devices on shared storage (e.g., NFS) when computing destination
storage requirements. Since these volumes are already on shared storage
they do not need to be migrated. As a result, migration fails if the
amount of free space on the shared drive is less than the size of the
volume to be migrated. The problem is addressed by adding a
block_device_info parameter to check_can_live_migrate_source() to allow
volumes to be filtered correctly when computing migration space
requirements.

This only fixes the issue on libvirt: it is unclear whether other
implementations suffer from the same issue.

Thanks to Florent Flament for spotting and fixing an issue while trying out
this patch.

(cherry picked from commit 42cae28241cd0c213201d036bfbe13fb118e4bee)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/virt/libvirt/test_libvirt.py
	nova/virt/driver.py
	nova/virt/hyperv/driver.py
	nova/virt/xenapi/driver.py

Co-Authored-By: Florent Flament <florent.flament@cloudwatt.com>
Closes-Bug: #1356552
Change-Id: Iac7d2cd2a70800fd89864463ca45c030c47411b0

commit_message:
Adding config hints for vanilla plugin

This change adds an implementation of the config hints for both versions
of the vanilla plugin.

Changes
* adding confighints_helper module to hold utility functions for
  creating the config hints
* adding edp engine for v2_6_0
* adding specific config hints functions for both vanilla edp_engine
  versions
* adding tests for vanilla config hints and hints helper

Change-Id: I3ae0eb94d380195708b1d4ca8f479dacf345212b
Partial-Implements: bp edp-job-types-endpoint

commit_message:
Adding config hints for HDP plugin

This changes adds HDP plugin configuration hints for both versions
(1.3.2 and 2.0.6).

Changes
* adding confighints_helper module to hold utility functions for
  creating the config hints
* adding specific config hints functions for both HDP edp_engine
  versions
* fixing inconsistencies in the oozie workflow_factory possible hints
  function
* adding tests for hdp config hints and hints helper

Change-Id: I7f85e47a4f9dfc7ccba0a5678701e5a4fb6742bb
Partial-Implements: bp edp-job-types-endpoint

commit_message:
Add mclient_remove=False parameter to batch node DELETE

This is to avoid restarting of offline nodes and just perform Cobbler
removal. This unifies the behavior with single node DELETE handler.

Closes-Bug: #1441571

Change-Id: Ia1ad993dbc32eedc2b7078963267d8758afb06c3

commit_message:
Authenticate once

Magnumclient authenticates twice when no token and no magnum url are
provided by the user. This change avoids the 2nd authentication.

Closes-Bug: #1442457
Change-Id: I9877e1be5d2e531442774ee4627bdfe1745781d7

commit_message:
Remove service entry from db when service is not found

Currently when delete for service fails with 404 status
from kubernetes, the service entry from db entry is not
deleted. But this should be removed from db.
Hence this patch handles the exception and let the
entry to be removed from db when not found.

Change-Id: I96552d41f32d7702b8a1353411d70cc9323de0b0
Closes-bug: 1426386

I think there is a bug in another place.
It seems like, kube_cli.rc_delete return False if kubectl command executes successfully. so I guess kube handler doesn't remove db entry."}, {'account_id': 10206, 'date': '2015-03-25 04:49:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Yuanying
I agree to your point. I have mentioned that point in comment#1 in https://bugs.launchpad.net/magnum/+bug/1426387

Here, it is two problems:

1. Deleting a existent resource, kubectl successfully deletes the resource but status returned to magnum is False, due to which db entry is not deleted.

2. Deleting a non-existent resource, no exception is raised from kubectl and status returned to magnum is True, due to which db entry is deleted.

So problem#1 is not a magnum issue. And problem#2 is not a problem indeed :)
But I am not sure that some other exception can be raised or not.

Hence, I think below two bugs should be closed as invalid:
https://bugs.launchpad.net/magnum/+bug/1426386
https://bugs.launchpad.net/magnum/+bug/1426387

And a new bug should be open to remove unnecessary handling of PodNotFound exception in pod_delete.'}, {'account_id': 10206, 'date': '2015-03-25 04:49:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Jay
Need your opinion on this.'}, {'account_id': 7049, 'date': '2015-03-25 07:59:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

1. The kubectl execute suessfully while you still hit false, it because you use old image. The old image packed with k8s 0.6.0.

@Sdake has updated image, so you need use the new image to get rid of that strange issue.

[fedora@testcontainer ~]$ kubectl delete pod redis-master -s http://192.168.1.231:8080
redis-master
[fedora@testcontainer ~]$ echo $?
0

2. For the second issue, when delete a non-exist pod, the kubectl really not throw any special condition.

>>> out, err = utils.trycmd('kubectl', 'delete', 'pod', 'ddd', '-s', 'http://192.168.1.231:8080')
>>> print err
Unexpected error while running command.
Command: kubectl delete pod ddd -s http://192.168.1.231:8080
Exit code: 255
Stdout: u''
Stderr: u'F0325 02:55:48.855824    3289 delete.go:79] pods "ddd" not found\n'
>>> 

You need parse err if you really want to what happened case for that. if not found or other wrong cases.


So for rc_delete, you need do as following


        if err:
            if ('pod "%s" not found' % name) in err:
                raise exception.PodNotFound(pod=name)
            else:
                return False

        return True

change related to rc, it would work, I think.'}, {'account_id': 7494, 'date': '2015-03-27 02:43:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Agree with Kai Qiang, you may want to get some similar logic from here: https://github.com/stackforge/magnum/blob/master/magnum/conductor/handlers/common/kube_utils.py#L150-L166 Thanks.'}, {'account_id': 668, 'date': '2015-03-28 08:21:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Remove rc entry from db when rc is not found

Currently when delete for rc fails with 404 status
from kubernetes, the rc entry from db entry is not
deleted. But this should be removed from db.
Hence this patch handles the exception and let the
entry to be removed from db when not found.

Change-Id: I78ff12e44709a270e7ab85f3d8e64adab3509885
Closes-bug: 1426387

commit_message:
Improve dos.py for manual manipulation with environment

Added new actions to dos.py:
 create               Create new environment
 slave-add            Add node to env
 slave-change         Change node vcpu and memory
 slave-remove         Remove node from environment
 admin-setup          Setup admin node

Change-Id: Ice795cda6179c4a6b6c1b869b4e74bcdaf6a5610
Blueprint: fuel-devops-manual-env-manipulation

commit_message:
Update puppet docs to match our CI

Fedora 21, RDO Kilo, etc.

Builtin k8s services "kubernetes" and "kubernetes-ro" caused port conflicts with
installed applications if they use ports 80 and/or 43

commit_message:
Move dependency's 'deploy' call into the method 'deploy' of app

It is wrong to call deploy from getContainer.
Calls were moved into method deploy of class for
all applications which have dependencies in properties.

Change-Id: I6643bf20d3e014c6d19d44896a041f523d52cb42
